1
00:02:41,246 --> 00:02:44,165
Well, here we are.
I turn down here at the next block.

2
00:02:44,582 --> 00:02:46,876
Thanks, mister. I'll get off there.

3
00:02:53,383 --> 00:02:56,386
- Want anything else?
- No.

4
00:02:56,469 --> 00:02:57,554
Hey, you.

5
00:03:00,557 --> 00:03:03,268
- Me?
- Yeah, you. Where ya heading?

6
00:03:04,561 --> 00:03:06,688
- East.
- Too bad.

7
00:03:07,564 --> 00:03:10,441
I thought if you was headin' north,
I might be able to help you out.

8
00:03:10,525 --> 00:03:13,278
Pushing to Salt Lake,
and I don't like to ride alone at night.

9
00:03:13,361 --> 00:03:16,030
I'm one of those guys that gotta talk
or I fall asleep.

10
00:03:16,114 --> 00:03:17,740
So I gotta get my--

11
00:03:17,824 --> 00:03:20,159
My partner,
he's got Lou to keep him company.

12
00:03:20,243 --> 00:03:21,911
But I ain't got nobody at all.

13
00:03:21,995 --> 00:03:24,622
- Where ya comin' from?
- West.

14
00:03:24,706 --> 00:03:27,333
Yeah, sure, I know,
but where? LA?

15
00:03:27,417 --> 00:03:29,794
- Maybe.
- Got a cousin out in LA.

16
00:03:29,878 --> 00:03:31,588
- You don't say?
- Yeah, he's been out —

17
00:03:33,047 --> 00:03:34,507
You're not much of a talker, are ya?

18
00:03:34,591 --> 00:03:36,509
My mother taught me
never to speak to strangers.

19
00:03:36,593 --> 00:03:38,428
- A wise guy?
- So what?

20
00:03:38,511 --> 00:03:42,432
Okay, okay. Don't get sore.
Just trying to be sociable, that's all.

21
00:03:43,892 --> 00:03:45,310
Hey, Glamorous.

22
00:03:45,393 --> 00:03:47,020
Give me change for a dime, will ya?

23
00:03:56,779 --> 00:03:58,823
Let's have something quieter this time, Joe.

24
00:03:58,907 --> 00:04:00,909
- My head's splitting.
- Is that what's wrong with it?

25
00:04:04,162 --> 00:04:07,749
- Done with your coffee?
- No. And don't rush me, will ya?

26
00:04:15,173 --> 00:04:17,175
Hey, turn that off.
Will ya turn that thing off?

27
00:04:17,258 --> 00:04:19,052
- What's eating you now?
- Yeah, what's eating you?

28
00:04:19,135 --> 00:04:21,054
- That music. It stinks!
- You don't like it?

29
00:04:21,137 --> 00:04:23,222
- No, turn it off!
- Now wait a minute, pal.

30
00:04:23,306 --> 00:04:24,974
That was my nickel, see?

31
00:04:25,058 --> 00:04:28,061
This is a free country,
and I play whatever I want to.

32
00:04:29,604 --> 00:04:30,647
Okay.

33
00:04:30,730 --> 00:04:33,024
Sure. And if you don't like,
you don't have to listen to it.

34
00:04:33,107 --> 00:04:35,068
And you can leave here anytime you wanna.

35
00:04:35,151 --> 00:04:36,694
Okay, okay. I'm sorry I asked.

36
00:04:36,778 --> 00:04:38,988
First good piece played tonight,
and you don't like it.

37
00:04:39,072 --> 00:04:41,491
Some people just ain't got any good taste.

38
00:04:52,752 --> 00:04:55,964
<i>That tune. That tune!</i>

39
00:04:56,047 --> 00:04:58,299
<i>Why was there always that rotten tune?</i>

40
00:04:58,383 --> 00:05:01,177
<i>Following me around, beating in my head,</i>
<i>never letting up.</i>

41
00:05:05,431 --> 00:05:07,183
<i>Did you ever wanna forget anything?</i>

42
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:10,520
<i>Did you ever wanna cut away</i>
<i>a piece of your memory or blot it out?</i>

43
00:05:10,979 --> 00:05:14,399
<i>You can't, you know?</i>
<i>No matter how hard you try.</i>

44
00:05:14,482 --> 00:05:16,442
<i>You can change the scenery,</i>

45
00:05:16,526 --> 00:05:18,611
<i>but sooner or later</i>
<i>you’ll get a whiff of perfume,</i>

46
00:05:18,695 --> 00:05:21,197
<i>or somebody will say a certain phrase</i>
<i>or maybe hum something.</i>

47
00:05:21,781 --> 00:05:23,533
<i>Then you're licked again.</i>

48
00:05:25,576 --> 00:05:27,996
<i>"I Can't Believe That You're in Love with Me."</i>

49
00:05:28,079 --> 00:05:29,956
<i>I used to love that song once.</i>

50
00:05:30,039 --> 00:05:33,126
<i>So did the customers back in the old</i>
<i>Break O' Dawn Club in New York.</i>

51
00:05:33,626 --> 00:05:36,713
<i>I can't remember a night when I didn’t get</i>
<i>at least three requests for it.</i>

52
00:05:37,505 --> 00:05:40,758
<i>Sue, she was always selling it too.</i>

53
00:05:41,259 --> 00:05:42,552
<i>Those were the days.</i>

54
00:06:07,702 --> 00:06:11,247
<i>♪ Your eyes of blue</i>
<i>Your kisses too ♪</i>

55
